This word is used before a noun that refers to space, a place, or to something that puts limits on something else, to show that the following noun includes something within it, contains something within it, or surrounds something:
examples: They were walking in the park (= The park limits where they were walking, and surrounds them or contains them). The horses were galloping in the field. She was still in bed when I came home. The doll is in the box; leave it there.

defs.def: This word is used before a noun that is abstract, cannot be touched, or refers to an occupation, interest, quality, characteristic, etc. It is used to show that the following noun includes or contains someone or something:
examples: He was an important character in the play (= The play includes this character). She worked in politics. In the last section of the book we list irregular verbs. There was a lot of evil in his personality.

defs.def: This word is used to show motion or direction from outside to a point within, and to mean "into'':

defs.def: This word is used before a noun that refers to a period of time, to show that something happens during that time, or occurs within a period or limit of that time:
examples: in ancient times (= something happened during ancient times). We did the task in only ten minutes. I love Paris in the autumn. We will be there in an hour. She is an actress in her twenties.

defs.def: This word is used with a following noun to show that the action, situation, condition, or manner of action is limited or described by that noun:

defs.def: This word is used with a noun, or a present participle form of a verb, to show what will result from some other action:

defs.def: energy, spirit, or animation:
examples: a man with a lot of go.

defs.def: a try at something;
examples: to have a go at winning the prize.

defs.def: a successful accomplishment;
examples: to make a go of a new business.

defs.def: a business agreement;
examples: Thirty dollars? It's a go.

defs.def: approval or permission, as to undertake or begin something:
examples: The boss gave us the go on the new project.

defs.def: a bout:
examples: the main go.

defs.def: from the very start;

examples: We tried to get there by noon, but it was no go.
Tomorrow's satellite launching is no go.
She's always on the go.

defs.def: (in calling the start of a race) start the race;
examples: On your mark! Get set! Go!

defs.def: ready.
functioning properly:
examples: two minutes before the satellite is to be launched and all systems are go.

defs.def: a Japanese game for two persons, played on a board having 361 intersections on which black and white stones or counters are alternately placed, the object being to block off and capture the opponent's stones and control the larger part of the board. Also called
general office.
general order.
a large mammal with solid hooves, used for carrying or pulling loads and for riding.
something on which a person rides, sits, or exercises, as if riding on the back of such an animal:
examples: [countable]a rocking horse.

defs.def: a wooden apparatus for exercising or performing gymnastics;
to eat a great deal.
from a source that can be trusted or believed:
examples: I got the news straight from the horse's mouth.
Hold your horses; we'll be there in a minute.

defs.def: to be critical of a gift.
a large, solid-hoofed, herbivorous quadruped,
a fully mature male animal of this type;

any of several odd-toed ungulates belonging to the family Equidae, including the horse, zebra, donkey, and ass, having a thick, flat coat with a narrow mane along the back of the neck and bearing the weight on only one functioning digit, the third, which is widened into a round or spade-shaped hoof.
something on which a person rides, sits, or exercises, as if astride the back of such an animal:
examples: rocking horse.

defs.def: Also called
carriage (def. 7).
soldiers serving on horseback;
examples: a thousand horse.

defs.def: a man;
Often,
the power or capacity to accomplish something, as by having enough money, personnel, or expertise:
examples: Our small company doesn't have the horses to compete against a giant corporation.

defs.def: a knight.
a crib, translation, or other illicit aid to a student's recitation;
a mass of rock enclosed within a lode or vein.
traveler (def. 6b).
a mold of a curved frame, esp. one used when the complexity of the curves requires laying out at full size.
heroin.
to be mistaken in judgment, esp. in backing a losing candidate.
or

examples: I have it straight from the horse's mouth that the boss is retiring.
Hold your horses! I'm almost ready.

defs.def: something entirely different. Also,
to be critical of a gift.
Mount your horse! Ride!
to provide with a horse or horses.
to set on horseback.
to set or carry on a person's back or on one's own back.
to cut notches for steps into (a carriage beam).
to move with great physical effort or force:
examples: It took three men to horse the trunk up the stairs.

defs.def: to place (someone) on a person's back, in order to be flogged.
to mount or go on a horse.
(of a mare) to be in heat.
to have coitus.
of, for, or pertaining to a horse or horses:
examples: the horse family; a horse blanket.

defs.def: drawn or powered by a horse or horses.
mounted or serving on horses:
examples: horse troops.

defs.def: unusually large.
a person or thing that removes or puts a head on something.
a reaping machine that cuts off and gathers only the heads of the grain.
a chamber to which the ends of a number of tubes are connected so that water or steam may pass freely from one tube to the other.
an exhaust manifold.
a plunge or dive headfirst, as into water:
examples: He stumbled and took a header into the ditch.

defs.def: a pass or shot made by heading the ball.
a sign that is part of or attached to the top of a rack displaying merchandise.
a line of information placed at the top of a page for purposes of identification.
